                text-shadow</a></li>          </ul>          <ul>            <li>Syntax: <i>text-shadow: (color) offsetX offsetY (blurRadius);</i></li>            <ul>              <li><i>color</i> and <i>blurRadius</i> are optional<i><br>                </i></li>            </ul>            <li>Example:<br>              <br>              <code>style="text-shadow: 5px 8px 1px;"<br>              </code>              <p style="text-shadow: 5px 8px 1px;"> This text has a shadow </p>            </li>          </ul>          <li>Box shadow</li>          <ul>            <li>Reference: <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-shadow?v=b"                target="_blank">MDN,
                box-shadow</a></li>            <li>Try it: <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/CSSref/css3_pr_box-shadow.asp">W3Schools,
                box-shadow</a><br>            </li>          </ul>        </ul>      </article>      <article id="topic2">        <p><u><b>IE Filters </b></u></p>        <ul>          <li> Older versions of Internet Explorer (prior to version 9) did not            support CSS 3 visual styles, but starting with IE 5.5, the browser            provided filters that could create visual effects.</li>          <li>Now (November, 2017), we probably don't need to worry about            supporting older versions of IE since versions older than IE 11,            which fully supports CSS3, are used by less than 1.5% of users            world-wide. <br>            <a href="https://www.stetic.com/market-share/browser/" target="_blank">Stetic
              Browser Statistics</a></li>        </ul>      </article>      <article id="topic3">        <p><b><u>Rotating Objects </u><br>          </b></p>        <ul>          <li>Tutorial: <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_3dtransforms.asp"              target="_blank">W3Schools,
              2D and 3D Rotation</a></li>        </ul>      </article>      <article id="topic4"> <u><b>Linear Gradients<br>          </b></u>        <ul>          <li>Tutorial: <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_gradients.asp"              target="_blank">W3Schools,
